caption: I love this bakery! The breads, cinnamon rolls, and sandwiches are all great. The owners and employees are super helpful and extremely kind. Always a great experience. Also if you are interested in starting to make your own sourdough bread, they have beginner friendly resources on their website and Facebook page.
WOW!!  Customer service was spot on.
Best sourdough! Lived in San Francisco for a time and have to say, I prefer Gulf Coast sourdough bread. Amazing!
LOVE their bread!! Whenever I visit my parents they request I bring a loaf from Gulf Coast with me :)
Best sandwiches in town with friendly staff too!! Highly recommend.
The breads are amazing. Sandwiches that cause your taste buds to have a party in your mouth. This is a jewel you don't want to miss.
Everything is fresh and the sourdough is awesome.
What a wonderful gem added to the area. Great food and wo derful staff make this an experience and not just a place to shop. If you're hungry on Friday try the pizza it's totally worth it!
Great sandwich even better cinnamon bun

Ordered one day and due to high volume there was a mix up on the order.  The staff corrected immediately  and were very gracious.  The sandwich was exceptional!  I can't wait to try more of their offerings.
This place is a real gem in the Tampa Bay area.  Artisan bread bakery and craft sandwiches and 'flybys'.   Absolute heaven!
If you’re in need of an awesome meal, this is the place to go! The environment and staff are amazing!

If you are a carb junkie like me, you are gonna want to try Gulf Coast Sourdough. When I come by I get one fresh loaf and several frozen loafs. The frozen ones stay great and defrost just fine. I love ALL of the bread I have had. Whenever I have company coming in from out of town, I make sure to have a cinnamon swirl loaf on hand for breakfast!
Great bakery. Enjoyed the Cinnamon Rolls. Love their breads.....
The service was incredible and so was the food!! The employees were soooo NICE!! Definitely coming back ♥️
Absolutely love this place! I’m not often in the area but when I am, I make a point to stop and get a hot, grilled sandwich. Keep up the great work!
Jesus Christ, this place is amazing. Incredible pricing for the best quality bread I've ever had. The flybys are a STEAL for how good they are, and how much food they are. This place is god-tier.

Great local spot if you're in the Seminole Heights area. I don't generally enjoy sourdough bread but checked this place out on the recommendation of a coworker. I'm so glad I did! Charming little eatery with just a couple of tables and chairs, most people probably take their orders to go, as I did. Staff was very friendly and knowledgeable, service was efficient and my order was correct. My sandwich was delicious. I haven't tried the Flyby yet, but since everyone that walked in the door was asking for them I am very much looking forward to it!

There were various types of sourdough rounds, baguettes, loaves and sourdough sweets.  I picked out a round and a baguette. I also grabbed some cans of King State canned cold brew. Then I set my sights on the real reason for this visit. Sandwiches!  Gulf Coast Sourdough has a couple vegan sandwich options. One is a Falafel Sandwich. The other, and the one I eventually settled on, is a vegan Flyby. Flybys are essentially Gulf Coast Sourdough's Oregano and Olive Oil dough rolled out and filled with a tasty filling then wrapped and baked. The vegan version contains vegetables like onions and spinach with a spicy kick. It was so good. I loved the puffiness of the dough, with a slight tang and the final kick. It came together perfectly.  The loaves that I took home with me were also great. They were crusty outside, soft inside and had a tanginess that outshines any sourdough you can find in the store. The price is a bit higher than if you bought one there, but not by much. The taste difference made the extra dollars worth it to me.  Like sourdough bread, sandwiches, unique desserts and local drinks? Gulf Coast Sourdough is somewhere you need to check out!

Soooo delicious. Ive had them multiple times and they are so so good. Their fresh bread, sandwiches, muffins, flybys, pizza, what have yous are making me drool for more! As soon as i take a bite my foot starts happy dancing. Thank you for your delicious foods!
Picked this place from the high reviews.  It didn't disappoint!!  Amazing!!

The smell of freshly baked goods when you go in? Absolutely DIVINE. Their bread is delicious, planning on coming back again when I need more baked goods. You should also try their falafel sandwich with kimchi. It may sound weird, but the combination is pretty dang good. I highly recommend coming here.
Very amazing food! It was honestly one of the best, most unique sandwiches I’ve ever had! I ordered the falafel sandwich btw.
Sandwiches were amazing. Place was super clean and everyone had masks on.

WOW!!  Best sandwiches we have had in a long time.  I had the meatball and my husband had the Italian. We will absolutely be going back.  Customer service was spot on. If I could give it more stars I would. Keep up the great work Gulf Coast!
Always a delicious experience. The best of the best. Recommended 100%
Omg!! So good!
This is such a special little place and I’m so happy it’s local to us! The sourdough is such a treat. We recently tried the vegan falafel flyby and it was fantastic. 100% would recommend!
Both sandwiches were so good I forgot to pay extra attention to the bread! Oh well, I guess I'll have to buy more sandwiches!

Really cool spot to have brunch and definitely coming back for dinner. I came with my sister and we sat inside. There is a nice outdoor vibey area if you sat outside. It was pretty windy when we came, but on my next visit I'll sit outside. We had Jaz as our waitress and she's very friendly, sincere, and knows much about the menu. We got the beet tacos with cheese for appetizers and I got the lamb tostada. The lamb was cooked perfectly and everything that was included in this dish was balanced and delicious. I know it came with cheese, tomatoes, red onion, cilantro, beans, and a fried egg sunny side up. Also had fresh cut fries on the side which was a great compliment to my dish. I eat an alright amount and I would say I could have shared it with another person so I don't feel overly stuffed.
Best sandwiches in town! Marina, Eva, and grant did a great job!
The best sourdough, lots of variations.  My favorites are the tumeric pepper and beach bread baguettes.  Oh, and the cinnamon rolls....delish!
The sanwiches were delicious.  We will definitely be back!

They are located in the heart of Seminole Heights. The location is absolutely welcoming and spacious enough to provide social distancing. Their baked goods are absolutely delicious and innovative. They are known for their Flybys and should give them a try on your visit. I find myself visiting them at least once every two weeks. Oh, you should definitely try their sourdough baguette. It is mind-blowing good and perfect for any type of sandwiches!
Best bread in town, get some
Absolutely the best sourdough bread around.  Their roasted red pepper bread is absolutely amazing.  Have been buying their products for years even before they had the store.
Best sourdough in the area!

Excellent owners and delicious loaves. Ive had several flybys and vegans should rejoice that the falafel hummus sauerkraut was surprisingly delicious. I was not a fan of the breakfast flyby as the eggs were extremely salty.
Best bread around! Highly recommend their flybys and dessert treats too.
Love it! Bread and flybys! Yum!
The chicken parm sandwich is awesome!   We also took home a loaf of sourdough and really enjoyed it.  But the cinnamon rolls stole the show.
Excellent food, Omgosh same owner but the food was delicious Paela with chicken duck and chorizo very good. Kale salad I leo eating more Calamares crunchy thin batter on black ink Delicious

Unbelievable Sourdough! So far I have tried the sourdough cinnamon rolls, sourdough baguette and the Italian sandwich on Asiago Sourdough and they were all outstanding. So many different doughs to choose from. Staff is super friendly and helpful. Did not have time to take a picture before I ate it all.

Delicious sandwiches and bread! A little pricey, but worth the drive. The only drawback is the location.  It is right on Nebraska, about 1 block S of Hillsborough Avenue so it comes up fast and parking is extremely limited. If this is the worst that you have to endure to get a really tasty sandwich and a large portion for 2 meals then I would absolutely go again!
Everything they make is delicious, you can't go wrong

Really fantastic selection of sandwiches and breads! Friendly staff and more than fair prices. Definitely worth going to a few times (or more) to see which sandwiches you like best. Itll be hard to pick!
I love their bread. If you are a carb queen, you need to check this place out. The rosemary bread is 🔥
Wow.  So good.  Very fast service.
Had an amazing Italian sandwich on their signature sourdough bread. Also bought a delicious loaf of cinnamon swirl....mmmmmmm.......cinnamon swirl. Love this place!!!
Nothing short of 5 stars. Came all the way down from Maryland, nothing compares to their customer service and food. A great business, should be a model for the whole restaurant industry.

First time trying this interesting bakery and sandwich shop.  I had a very tasty Italian on Simply Sourdough.  The sandwich was pressed with spinach and tomatoes.  They have a nice selection of different flavor sourdoughs and even hand packed bags of bread flour for anyone baking their own.  I’ll definitely be back.

Hands-down best place to get great quality sourdough To take home and fresh made sandwiches. Sam and Brie are the sweetest employees and always make my trip there even better! Gulf coast sourdough is amazing
Great place to pickup flour and starter for making great sourdough bread.
I love this place! So many bread "flavors" to choose from, every sandwich I've tried is fabulous, and the cinnamon rolls are dense and delicious. Highly recommend this place. ❤️
Cute little spot! Big fan, love the cinnamon rolls!
If your a bread eater this is the place
Small space but it serves the purpose.  Great sourdough breads.  We made Reubens with the Funkernickel & the Marbeled Rye.
Be warned, once you try their sandwiches you'll be back! Love the bread and the opportunity to buy it frozen and save a little money!
Fantastic bread shop! Everything is amazing! I took their bread baking class and learned SO much!
Great place!  Friendly people,  bread is wonderful, and sandwiches are so flavorful.
Really good vegan tacos, good beer selection, and fun atmosphere! Can get crowed at night and on the weekend.

Just found this place while dropping my bike off across the street.  Closed on Monday so made the trip back on Tuesday to try on of these 'flyby's.'  Absolutely delicious.  Can't wait to go back and try other items.  Very friendly staff and what I've tried so far was amazing.
Always great service and great food. Five stars for me!

quality ingredients, supplied by courteous and knowledgeable staff. you can sence the passion provided by each member once you walk through the door. the menu was overflowing with delicious sounding items making this a must visit again cafe.
Best sourdough bread ever. I am so happy to have found this place. Buying all my bread here.
Amazing bread and amazing people!

Absolutely love this local bakery! I buy 2 loaves of sourdough every couple weeks & keep them on the freezer. When I’m ready to eat, I simply throw it in the toaster for a couple minutes & it is as fresh & delicious as when I first bought it. The flavors are unique & always amazing. I’ve been by their shop in Seminole Heights for sandwiches & even all purpose flour. Always a great experience & I would highly recommend!
Fresh and delicious sandwiches and very friendly service!
Best bread and sammiches hands down! You gotta try it!

I originally took a sourdough bread class put on by Gulf Coast before the shop opened. The class was great, and I have made many loaves using the starter I got from that class. Since then, I’ve been to the restaurant multiple times, and have been more than satisfied every time. The Flybys are fantastic, and if you get a sandwich, you can pick from their different breads. They also sell bread, and it hold up really well in the freezer! Go, for the food and the class, you won’t be disappointed.

We came on a Saturday morning and got a vegetarian flyby (falafel and kraut) and an Italian sandwich on rosemary bread. The flyby was good, would be interested in trying different flavors. But this Italian sandwich was perfection. It was just a perfectly, well crafted Italian sandwich with high quality ingredients and made with care and attention to detail. It is exactly what a sandwich should be. Everyone there was friendly and helpful. Great food, great people, great place. Definitely support this shop. I can’t wait to try their chocolate babka, cinnamon roll, turmeric bread, and more sandwiches next time!

Ok, fly bys, sandwiches and cinnamon rolls would be enough. But they also sell killer take home loaves, and bags of bread crisps that are superior salad croutons. Go on Wednesday. Trust me. Get a sandwich. The Sriracha bread is sandwich gold. The rye made me cry. Good cry!
The center of the universe for bread and sandwiches. WOW and wow!
Bread is amazing but I was disappointed by the size of the flybys. For $7, I expected them to be about double the size they were.

Love everything about this place. Love the background story and they are good at what they do. If I was a local I would crave this place. I ordered the 3 cheese grilled cheese on siracha garlic. Simple concept but delicious! And you can buy their bread to take home. :)

You will be hooked! Their bread is unlike anything around and their pepperoni rolls or fly-bys are the best! They have tons of vegetarian options as well. Local owners too which is added bonus supporting the community! Highly recommend!

I signed up for a sourdough baking class through this amazing place. It was such a great experience. The owners are incredible and so knowledgeable. I sampled a lot of the brow and it's some of the best I've ever had. Looking forward to visiting  for one of their amazing sandwiches.
Great sandwiches and coffee.  Pretty quick too!
Awesome & filling!
Their breakfast flybys are simple the BEST breakfast sandwich I have ever had!!  I will be back. ALOT!!
They have the most amazing vegan bread. Need to go back and try their sandwiches that everyone talks about. Also they are the sweetest peeps. Love love love.
Great stuff. It was a little confusing for me the first time but I asked for help and a young lady showed me how to navigate the small shop. Very, very good sandwiches and great bread.
The Gulf Coast Sourdough Sandwich Shop has a wide array of breads to choose from. No matter what you choose, you can't go wrong. This place has a nice and helpful staff.

I drive 30 miles round trip for the best sourdough bread and the home made sauerkraut in the Tampa Bay area. All the products are made fresh daily and very healthy for longevity and taste great. Thank you for all the time and effort to create quality food products.
Awesome food, great bread and flyby's.  Stop by if you have the chance, everyone is very friendly as well!

Another great Seminole Heights spot! First off, the bread itself is wonderful, as are the cinnamon rolls. But the sandwiches are why we keep going back. They specialize in what they call "Tampa pressed" sandwiches, which I really like. But they'll also do them un-pressed by request, which my partner always does, and I admit it's really good that way too if you prefer your bread un-toasted like her. My favorite so is the Greek turkey. Or maybe the pizza sandwich. Or whatever the special of the day is. It's all great.

I have been buying bread from Gulf Coast Sourdough for years but yesterday was my first time at the new sandwich shop. Of course I had to buy several loaves of bread to take home. Then ordered a flyby and a sandwich to eat here. Both the sandwich and the flyby were really good.  My son who is usually very picky eater commented on the pepperoni flyby with "that's yummy" - which is a compliment that he does not give lightly. We will definitely be back soon!

Best bread in Tampa! The bread freezes really well, so we always stock up; our go to flavors are Roasted Red Pepper, Sriracha Garlic, and Asiago for all of our sandwiches whether made in store or made at home. The cinnamon rolls are to die for and their cinnamon swirl bread turns into amazing french toast! This is definitely a Tampa gem. ❤

There are not enough stars for the chocolate babka.   I also love the huge round loaf of sourdough.  That was great for some avo toast.   Wasn't a fan of the olive oil baguette.  But happy to have this fabulous bakery nearby, for my weekend bread runs.
This place is exactly what Seminole Heights needs. Their bread is delicious. Buy local.
Great cinnamon rolls and yummy bread! Staff is very friendly!!
It's not a bread revolution if only the wealthy can afford it.

Wonderful sandwiches, very happy that we have a local shop just down the road! Have tried the turkey pesto, Greek, turkey and chips/hummus. All have been delicious and made with care. Look for them at the weekend markets in Seminole Heights, Hyde Park and DTSP!

I've worked with their product at Oxford Exchange which was awesome and now I'm able to use them in my own menu items now. Very kind and welcoming. They really work with you and are prompt and on point with their product. I recommend them to anyone who wants great bread and great service. Cheers!!
Great sandwiches and delicious sourdough to take home!
Fresh ingredients, delicious breakfast sandwiches!

Visited your establishment last Wednesday for lunch ...I ordered the pizza  grilled sandwich and received a free cinnamon roll. The sandwich and roll was delicious! I went back to the counter and purchases a cinnamon bread loaf-Yum the be t
Been eating their amazing bread for years! So happy they finally got their own shop. The sandwiches are unique, fresh and of course delicious!!
Great bread, great people! Sandwiches are wonderful also.  Small space, so if you come for the sandwiches, be prepared to carry out.  They do have a few tables, so you might get lucky.

Very friendly, and the bread tastes of sour-y goodness!  When we moved here from California we had a hard time finding sourdough that actually tasted sour and not just like white bread.  They have real, delicious sour tasting bread!  They also have variety if you're looking for more than just sourdough.  They have a saracha garlic, cinnamon roll bread, and more that we haven't tried!  10/10, would recommend!

Nice little surprise awaits you in  Seminole Heights.  I  just happened upon the sign outside today and I turned around and went back, so glad I did  this sourdough sandwich shop is perfect for the area it's in. I was greeted warmly,  and shown the menu.  And chose the Bacon,spinach, and tomatoes on pressed sourdough. Each sandwich is custom built to order.  It was a great sandwich,  pressed to  perfection, full of flavor,  the spinach was a wonderful idea.  I would recommend this sandwich for any one.  As well as the shop itself.   The menu is limited,  they offer  loaves of bread that they freshly  baked there.   They accept cash and credit.  And call in orders.

There’s ALWAYS a first time for everything... and surely won’t be my last!! Great flavors, fresh in-house baked bread and a locally-produced-supportive company 👌🏼  P.S.: On Wednesdays you’ll be served a complimentary cinnamon roll !! 🤫😝 #SOOgood

Best bread in the bay area.   Great people who take real pride in their baking and deliver amazing loaves like sriracha garlic and traditional sourdough.  The eat-in area is a bit small and warm,  but the food more than makes up for it.   The sandwiches are hearty and delicious, and anything baked is on point (try the cinnamon roll!).  Do yourself a favor and get a takeout sandwich - they're delicious.
If you knew what was best for you, youd swing by for a bacon egg and cheese “flyby”. Unreal delicious!  If you like sourdough bread, this place is the best in town!
Get the Roni Flyby! I can and will get one every time I go near the Sandwich House! If I could give 10 stars I would.

We've tried the sourdough and marbled rye and they were both so delicious.  When we were checking out I grabbed one of the heated savory pastries (I can't remember what they are called), but we got the spinach & feta.  Warm, loaded with spinach and just the right amount of feta (I don't like too much because it tends to overpower the other ingredients).  We are headed back to try the pepperoni one next, and of course pick up some more delicious bread.  This place rocks.  Very friendly staff too.
Absolutely fantastic bread, tasty sandwiches.
It is disgustingly hot in there

Had an amazing pastrami sandwich here. Probably one of the best sandwiches I've had in Tampa. The bread chips and hummus were tasty also. Service was good too, everyone was very helpful and friendly. Would recommend to anyone looking for a good sandwich.

Being a Carbie Barbie, I am very excited to have Gulf Coast Sourdough planting their roots in Seminole Heights with the perfect addition of a sandwich shop. But it’s so much more! Brett and Christina are the nicest people you could ever meet and they’re so open to suggestions which means you always see new items they’re experimenting with. I love everything I’ve eaten so far and can’t wait to keep going back. Join the Bread Revolution!

I guess you could say my girlfriend and I are sandwich connoisseurs, so we wanted to give this place a try. We loved it! I ordered a traditional ham and swiss while she had an egg sandwich, both were delicious and generously stuffed with the fixings. We will definitely be back and welcome this little gem to the neighborhood.

I've been visiting GCS at local markets for a while now, and I'm so happy they have a brick and mortar shop now! Their food is amazing! I got the falafel sandwich on the red pepper bread with kimchi 😍😍

Found this gem when I read an article in the paper. Authentic sourdough and super nice staff. Cinnamon buns are key for a great breakfast bite. Breakfast sandwiches are great and full of flavor. I highly recommend this place. They have a farmers market following and have been around for about 4 years. Glad to see they made it to the heights!!
Legitimately the best bread in Tampa. Sriracha garlic and black pepper tumeric are especially delicious.
Amazing spinach and feta flyby. The chips and hummus were tasty and cheap! Good bread selection!
They have the best breads in Tampa Bay, coming in for toast and coffee this rainy morning was the best idea i've had all week!
Great food and good folks. Can't wait to try the breakfast!
